                <div class="gallery-heading-wrap">
                    <div class="gh-number">8</div>
                    <h2 class="cat-nine">&#039;The Bard&#039;s Tale&#039;</h2>
                </div>
                                    <div class="g-image-mask lightbox-trigger"
                         item-number="8"
                         rel="http://images.guff.com/gallery/image/no84"
                         rel-href="/classic-video-games-in-desperate-need-of-a-remake/the-bards-tale">
                        <img class="pris-lazy-load" data-original="http://images.guff.com/gallery/image/no84"
                             rel="&lt;p class=&quot;fr-tag&quot;&gt;Released in 2004, &lt;em&gt;The Bard’s Tale&lt;/em&gt; was essentially a parody of video games, and RPG’s in particular. The game was known for skewering tropes such as animals having money and treasures, and people apparently being okay with sword wielding teenagers wandering into their houses. These cliché concepts still exist in virtually every RPG, proving the parody may not have been biting enough. With another 11 years of video games having been made, countless more clichés have been created as well, and all of them are ready to be parodied.&lt;/p&gt;">
                        <div class="clicktoenlarge"><i class="fa fa-expand"></i></div>
                    </div>
                                <div class="g-text-wrap">
                    <span class="g-subtext">&#039;The Bard&#039;s Tale&#039;</span>
                    <div class="description"><p class="fr-tag">Released in 2004, <em>The Bard’s Tale</em> was essentially a parody of video games, and RPG’s in particular. The game was known for skewering tropes such as animals having money and treasures, and people apparently being okay with sword wielding teenagers wandering into their houses. These cliché concepts still exist in virtually every RPG, proving the parody may not have been biting enough. With another 11 years of video games having been made, countless more clichés have been created as well, and all of them are ready to be parodied.</p></div>

                    <div class="share-comment-wrap">
                                                    <a href="http://www.androidtapp.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/The-Bards-Tale-Witty-narration-throughout.png"target="_blank" class="source">
                                <span>source</span> <i class="fa fa-link"></i>
                            </a>
                                                <a class="sc-share btn-share" data-type="facebook" data-action="share"
                           data-url="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=SHARE_URL">Share <i class="fa fa-share"></i></a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </article>

            
            
            
