            <div class="thumbnail list-post-item">
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-sm-12">
                        <h1 class="post-title">Classic Video Games in Desperate Need of a Remake</h1>
                                                    <div class="byline">Published
                                <span title="November 8, 2015"
                                      data-livestamp="1446991502">November 8, 2015
                                </span> | By <a href="http://guff.com/author/contributing-writer-lucas">Lucas Snipes</a>
                            </div>
                                                <hr>
                        <div class="ad-container adzerk-desktop-ad no-margin" data-adzerk-desktop-id="2"></div>
                        <hr>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="current-list-item-container">
                    <div class="current-item-title">
                        <h3><span class="current-item-index-title">1.</span> &#039;E.T.&#039;</h3>
                        <div class="current-item-index-container">
                            <span class="current-item-index">1</span><span>/15</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="list-post-image-container perf-image-container">
                        <div class="loader-container hidden">
                            <div class="loader-inner">
                                <div></div>
                                <div></div>
                                <div></div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                                                    <img class="pris-lightbox lightbox-trigger desktop-performance-img"
                                 data-item-number="0"
                                 rel="http://images.guff.com/gallery/image/no14"
                                 rel-href="/classic-video-games-in-desperate-need-of-a-remake/e-t1"
                                 src="http://images.guff.com/gallery/image/no14"
                                 data-desc="&lt;p class=&quot;fr-tag&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;E.T.&lt;/em&gt; for the Atari 2600 is generally considered the worst video game of all time. The main issue was that production was rushed, and the game turned from a fun tie-in with the movie where you got to go on adventures as the world’s most famous alien into a game where that alien falls into holes. A lot. But if a good team was put behind it, &lt;em&gt;E.T.&lt;/em&gt; could still be a viable franchise. It just needs to be remade in a way that includes an actual plot and gameplay, and absolutely anything at all other than falling into holes. Although falling into a land fill in New Mexico might be a neat Easter egg for fans.&lt;/p&gt;"
                                 rel-desc="&#039;E.T.&#039;">
                        
                        <a class="prev-item json_load inactive"
                           data-direction="prev"
                           data-href="/classic-video-games-in-desperate-need-of-a-remake">
                            <i class="fa fa-chevron-left fa-fw"></i>
                        </a>

                        <a class="next-item json_load"
                                                          data-href="/classic-video-games-in-desperate-need-of-a-remake/michael-jackson-s-moonwalker"
                                                      data-direction="next">
                            <i class="fa fa-chevron-right fa-fw"></i>
                        </a>
                                            </div>

                    <div class="list-item-text">
                        <div class="description"><p class="fr-tag"><em>E.T.</em> for the Atari 2600 is generally considered the worst video game of all time. The main issue was that production was rushed, and the game turned from a fun tie-in with the movie where you got to go on adventures as the world’s most famous alien into a game where that alien falls into holes. A lot. But if a good team was put behind it, <em>E.T.</em> could still be a viable franchise. It just needs to be remade in a way that includes an actual plot and gameplay, and absolutely anything at all other than falling into holes. Although falling into a land fill in New Mexico might be a neat Easter egg for fans.</p></div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="current-item-footer">
                        <div class="current-item-index-container">
                            <span class="current-item-index">1</span><span>/15</span>
                        </div>

                        <a href="http://cdn0.vox-cdn.com/assets/4554361/ET-Game.jpg" target="_blank" class=" source">
                            <span>source</span>
                        </a>

                        <div class="share-this-container">
                            <a class="btn-share" data-type="facebook" data-action="share" data-url="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=SHARE_URL">
                                <div class="share-button facebook">
                                    <i class="fa fa-facebook fa-fw fa-lg"></i> Share
                                </div>
                            </a>
                            <a class="btn-share" data-type="twitter" data-action="tweet" data-url="http://twitter.com/home?status=SHARE_URL">
